obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68114)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called "The Chutia Nagpur Encumbered Estates Act, 1876."`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68114&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68116)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Power to vest management of property in an officer appointed by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68116&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line Whenever
  line `any holder of immoveable property, or (when such holder is a minor, or of unsound mind, or an idiot) his`
  line `guardian, committee or other legal curator,`
  line
  line `or the person who would be heir to such holder if he died intestate,`
  line
  line `or (when such person is a minor, or of unsound mind, or an idiot) his guardian, committee or other legal`
  line curator,
  line
  line `or when any such property belonging to such holder has been attached in execution of a decree of a`
  line `Civil Court, the Deputy Commissioner within whose jurisdiction such property is situate,`
  line
  line `applies in writing to the Commissioner, stating that the holder of the said property is subject to, or that`
  line `his said property is charged with, debts or liabilities other than debts due, or liabilities incurred, to`
  line `Government, and requesting that the provisions of this Act be applied to his case,`
  line
  line `the Commissioner may, with the previous consent of the Lieutenant-Governor of Bengal, by order`
  line `published in the Calcutta Gazette, appoint an officer (hereinafter called the Manager), and vest in him the`
  line `management of the whole or any portion of the immoveable property of or to which the said holder is then`
  line `possessed or entitled in his own right, or which he is entitled to redeem, or which may be acquired by or`
  line `devolve on him or his heir, during the continuance of such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68117)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Effect of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68117&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the such publication the following consequences shall ensue:--`
  line
  line `Bar of suits.--First, all proceedings which may then be pending in any Civil Court in British India, in`
  line `respect to such debts or liabilities, shall be barred; and all processes, executions and attachments for or in`
  line `respect of such debts and liabilities shall become null and void;`
  line
  line `Freedom from arrest.--Secondly, so long as such management continues, the holder of the said`
  line `property and his heir shall not be liable to arrest for or in respect of the debts and liabilities to which the`
  line `said holder was immediately before the said publication subject, or with which the property so vested as`
  line `aforesaid or any part thereof was at the time of the said publication charged, other than debts due, or`
  line `liabilities incurred, to Government,`
  line
  line `Moveable property not liable to attachment for prior debts.--nor shall their movable property be`
  line `liable to attachment or sale, under process of any Civil Court in British India, for or in respect of such debts`
  line `and liabilities other than as aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `Cessation of power to alienate. --Thirdly, so long as such management continues,`
  line
  line `(a) the holder of the said immoveable property and his heir shall be incompetent to mortgage, charge,`
  line `lease or alienate their immoveable property or any part thereof, or to grant valid receipts for the rents and`
  line `profits arising or accruing therefrom,`
  line
  line `Immoveable property freed from attachment.--(b) such property shall be exempt from attachment`
  line `or sale under such process as aforesaid except for or in respect of debts due, or liabilities incurred, to`
  line `Government, and`
  line
  line `Cessation of power to contract.--(c) the holder of the same property and his heir shall be incapable`
  line `of entering into any contract which may involve them, or either of them, in pecuniary liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68119)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Manager to receive rents and profits, and pay therefrom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68119&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall, during his management of the said`
  line `immoveable property, receive and recover all rents and profits due in respect thereof; and shall, upon`
  line `receiving such rents and profits, give receipts for the same.`
  line
  line `From the sums so received, he shall pay--`
  line
  line `and pay therefrom the Government demand, First, the Government revenue, and all debts of`
  line `liabilities for the time being due or incurred to Government;`
  line
  line `rent due to superior landlord, Secondly, in the case of under-tenures, the rent (if any) due to the`
  line `superior landlord, in respect of the said property:`
  line
  line `annual sum for maintenance of holder of property and his heir, Thirdly, such annual sums as`
  line `appears to the Commissioner requisite for the maintenance of the holder of the property, his heir, and their`
  line `families:`
  line
  line `costs of repairs and improvements, Fourthly the costs of such repairs and improvements of the`
  line `property as appear necessary to the Manager and are approved by the Commissioner:`
  line
  line `cost of management and the debt and liabilities, and the residue shall be applied in discharge of the`
  line `costs of the management, and in settlement of such debts and liabilities of the holder of the property and`
  line `his heir, as may be established under the provision hereinafter contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68121)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notice to claimants against holder of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68121&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On the publication of the order vesting in him the`
  line `management on the said property, the manager shall publish a notice in English, Urdu and Hindi, calling`
  line `upon all persons having claims against the holder of the said property to notify the same in writing to such`
  line `Manager within three months from the date of the publication.`
  line
  line `Notice how published.--Such notice shall be published by being posted at the kachahris in the district`
  line `or districts in which the said property lies, and at such other places as the Manager thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68122)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Claim to contain full particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68122&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every such claimant shall, along with his claim present full`
  line `particulars thereof.`
  line
  line `Documents to be given up.--Every document on which the claimant founds his claim, or on which he`
  line `relies in support thereof, shall be delivered to the Manager along with the claim.`
  line
  line `Entries in Books.--If the document be an entry in any book, the claimant shall produce the book to`
  line `the Manager, together with a copy of the entry on which he relies. The Manager shall mark the book for the`
  line `purpose of identification, and, after examining and comparing the copy with the original, shall return the`
  line `book to the claimant.`
  line
  line `Exclusion of documents not produced.--If any document in the possession or under the control of`
  line `the claimant is not delivered or produced by him to the Manager along with the claim, the Manager may`
  line `refuse to receive such document in evidence on the claimant's behalf at the investigation of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (68123)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Debt not duly notified to be barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68123&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every debt or liability other than debts due, or`
  line `liabilities incurred, to Government or (in the case of under-tenures), the rent due to the superior landlord,`
  line `to which the holder of the property is subject, or with which the property is charged, and which is not duly`
  line `notified to the Manager within the time and in manner hereinbefore mentioned, shall be barred:`
  line
  line `Provision for admission of claim within further period of nine months.--Provided that, when proof`
  line `is made to the Manager that the claimant was unable to comply with the provisions of sections five and six,`
  line `the Manager may admit his claim within the further period of nine months from the expiration of the said`
  line `period of three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (68124)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Determination of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68124&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall, in accordance with the rules to be made under this`
  line `Act, determine the amount of all principal debts and liabilities justly due to the several creditors of the`
  line `holder of the property, and to persons holding mortgages, charges or liens thereon, and the interest (if any)`
  line `due at the date of such determination, in respect of such debts and liabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (68125)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to inquire into consideration for leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68125&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `If such property or any part thereof be in the`
  line `possession of any person claiming to hold it under a lease, dated within the three years immediately`
  line `preceding the publication of the order mentioned in section two, the Manager, with the sanction of the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner and Commissioner (or of the Commissioner only if the Deputy Commissioner be`
  line `himself the Manager), may inquire into the sufficiency of the consideration for which the lease was given;`
  line
  line `Power to set aside leases.-- and, if such consideration appears to him insufficient, may by order either`
  line `set aside the lease or cause the person so in possession to pay such consideration for the said lease as the`
  line `Manager thinks fit, and in default of such payment the lease or shall be cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (68127)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appeal to Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68127&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `An appeal against any refusal, admission, determination or`
  line `order under section six, seven, eight or nine shall lie, if preferred within six weeks from the date thereof to`
  line `the Deputy Commissioner within whose jurisdiction the property is situate, and the decision of the manager,`
  line `if no such appeal has been so preferred, shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Deputy Commissioner be himself the Manager, the appeal shall lie to the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `Appeal to commissioner.--An appeal shall lie from any decision of the Deputy Commissioner, if`
  line `preferred within six weeks of the date of his decision, to the Commissioner, and the decision of such`
  line `Commissioner, or of the Deputy Commissioner if no such appeal has been so preferred, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68128)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Scheme for settlement of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68128&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When the amount due in respect of the debts and liabilities`
  line `mentioned in section eight has been finally determined, the Manager shall prepare and submit to the`
  line `Commissioner a schedule of such debts and liabilities, and a scheme for the settlement thereof; and such`
  line `scheme, when approved by the Commissioner, shall be carried into effect.`
  line
  line `Power to return scheme for revision.--Until such approval is given, the Commissioner may, as often`
  line `as he thinks fit, send back such scheme to the Manager for revision, and direct him to make such further`
  line `inquiry as may be requisite for the proper preparation of the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (68129)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Restoration of owner to his property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68129&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `When all such debts and liabilities have been discharged,`
  line `or if, within six months after the publication of the order mentioned in section two, the Commissioner`
  line `thinks that the provisions of this Act should not continue to apply to the case of the holder of the said`
  line `property or his heir,`
  line
  line `such holder or his heir shall be restored to the possession and enjoyment of the property, or of such part`
  line `thereof as has not been sold by the Manager under the power contained in section eighteen, but subject to`
  line `the leases and mortgages (if any) granted and made by the Manager under the powers hereinafter contained.`
  line
  line `Restoration to be notified. Revival of barred proceedings and debts. Reinstatement of`
  line `mortgagees.--Where the holder of the property or his heir is so restored under the circumstances`
  line `mentioned in the second clause of this section,such restoration shall be notified in the Calcutta Gazette, and`
  line `thereupon the proceedings, processes, executions, any attachments mentioned in section three (so far as`
  line `they relate to debts and liabilities which the Manager has not paid off or compromised), and the debts and`
  line `liabilities barred by section seven, shall be revived; and any mortgagee or conditional vendee dispossessed`
  line `under section sixteen shall be reinstated, unless his claim under the mortgage or conditional sale has been`
  line satisfied;
  line
  line `Period of limitation as to revived proceedings and debts.--and in calculating the periods of`
  line `limitation applicable to such revived proceedings, and to suits to recover and enforce such revived debts`
  line `and liabilities, the time intervening between such restoration and the publication of the order mentioned in`
  line `section two, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (68131)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to call for further particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68131&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The manager may, from time to time, call for further and`
  line `more detailed particulars of any claim preferred before him under this Act, and may at his discretion refuse`
  line `to proceed with the investigation of the claim until such particulars are supplied.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (68132)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to summon witnesses and compel production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68132&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this`
  line `Act, the Manager may summon and enforce the attendance of witnesses and compel them to give evidence,`
  line `and compel the production of documents by the same means, and, as far as possible, in the same manner,`
  line `as is provided in the case of a Civil Court by the Code of Civil Procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (68133)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Investigation to be deemed a judicial proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68133&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every investigation conducted by the Manager`
  line `with reference to any claim preferred before him under this Act, or to any matter connected with any such`
  line `claim, shall be taken to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code.`
  line
  line `Statements of persons examined to be evidence.--And every statement made by any person`
  line `examined by or before the Manager with reference to such investigation, whether upon oath or otherwise,`
  line `shall be taken to be evidence within the meaning of the same Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (68134)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Manager to have powers of holder of estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68134&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall have, for the purpose of`
  line `realizing and recovering the rents and profits of the said immovable property, the same powers as the holder`
  line `of the property would have had for such purpose if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `Power to remove mortgagee or conditional vendee in possession.--And if such property, or any part`
  line `thereof, be in the possession of any mortgagee or conditional vendee, the Manager may apply to the Court`
  line `of the Deputy Commissioner within whose jurisdiction the property is situate, and such Court shall cause`
  line `the same to be delivered to the Manager as if a decree therefor had been made in his favour, but without`
  line `prejudice to the mortgagee or vendee preferring his claim under the provisions hereinbefore contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (68135)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68135&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules made under Section 19, the Manager shall have power to`
  line `demise all or any part of the property under his management for any term of years not exceeding twenty`
  line `years absolute, to take effect in possession in consideration of any fine or fines, or without fine and reserving`
  line `such rents and under such conditions as may be agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (68136)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to raise money by mortgage or sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68136&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Manager, with the previous assent of the`
  line `Commissioner, shall have power to raise any money which may be required for the settlement of the debts`
  line `and liabilities (other than as aforesaid) to which the holder of the property is subject, or with which such`
  line `property or any part thereof is charged,`
  line
  line `by demising by way of mortgage the whole or any part of such property for a term not exceeding twenty`
  line `years from the said publication,`
  line
  line `or by selling, with the previous consent of the holder of the property and of the person (being of full`
  line `age) who would be his heir if he died intestate, by public auction or by private contract, and upon such`
  line `terms as the Manager thinks fit, such portion of the same property as may appear expedient.`
  line
  line `And no mortgagee advancing money upon any mortgage made under this section, shall be bound to see`
  line `that such money is wanted, or that no more than is wanted is raised.`
  line
  line `Manager’s receipts.--And the receipt of the Manager for any monies paid to him as such, shall`
  line `discharge the person paying the same therefrom and from being concerned to see to the application thereof.`
  line `The power to mortgage conferred by this section shall not be exercisable until six months have elapsed`
  line `from the publication of the order mentioned in section two.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (68138)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68138&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Lieutenant-Governor of Bengal may, from time to time, make rules`
  line `consistent with this Act to regulate the following matter:--`
  line
  line `(a) the security to be required from subordinate officers under this Act,`
  line
  line `(b) the notices to be given under this Act and the publication of such notices,`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed in determining under section eight the debts and liabilities due to`
  line `creditors and other persons, and in performing the other duties imposed on any officer by this Act,`
  line
  line `(d) the allowance of interest on each of the principal debts and liabilities so determined, from the`
  line `date on which it was incurred down to the date of the determination, and on the aggregate amount of`
  line `such debts and liabilities from the date of the determination down to the date of payment,`
  line
  line `(e) the order of paying debts and liabilities so determined;`
  line
  line `and generally for the guidance of officers in all matters connected with the enforcement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Such rules, when approved by the Governor General in Council and published in the Calcutta`
  line `Gazette, shall have the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (68139)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to appoint new Managers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68139&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Commissioner thinks fit, he may appoint any`
  line `officer to be a Manager instead of any Manager appointed under this Act; and thereupon the property then`
  line `vested under this Act in the former Manager shall become vested in the new Manager.`
  line
  line `Every such new Manager shall have the same powers as if he had been originally appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (68140)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Managers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68140&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Every Manager appointed under this Act shall be deemed a`
  line `public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (68141)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Bar of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68141&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other proceeding shall be maintained against any person in respect of`
  line `anything done by him bona fide pursuant to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (68142)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Saving of jurisdiction of Courts in Chutia Nagpur in respect of certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68142&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this`
  line `Act precludes the Courts in Chutia Nagpur having jurisdiction in suits relating to the succession to, or`
  line `claims of maintenance from, any immoveable property brought under the operation of this Act, from`
  line `entertaining and disposing of such suits; but to all such suits the Manager of such property shall be made a`
  line party.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (68143)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Act not to affect powers conferred by Bengal Act II of 1869.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941&sectionId=68143&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00094_187606_1663821910941
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be`
  line `deemed to take away or abridge any power or authority conferred by an Act passed by the LieutenantGovernor of Bengal in Council, entitled “\"An Act to ascertain, regulate and record certain tenures in Chutia Nagpur," on any person appointed to be a Special Commissioner thereunder, or on the Commissioner of`
  line `the division of Chutia Nagpur.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
